 similar to lists in that they help to organize data, but their use, limitations, and syntax are 
 different from typical python lists. They are easier to access in my opinion, because they require 
 a keyword to access the data, rather than just the datas numerical position in a list, whihc can be 
 very helpful for accessing dictionary data when the user cannot remember its specific numerical position. 
 While lists are faster due to their index based format, the memory of keywords is faster for people who 
 dont desire to learn and memorize their datas position in a list. """